Joe Buck is an American sportscaster who is best known for his work as a play-by-play announcer for Major League Baseball, the National Football League, and other sports broadcasts. He was born on April 25, 1969, in St. Petersburg, Florida, and is the son of the late legendary sportscaster Jack Buck.
Buck began his broadcasting career as a teenager, working in local radio and television stations in the St. Louis area. He eventually landed a job with Fox Sports in 1994, where he has been a mainstay ever since. In addition to his work with Fox, Buck has also called games for HBO Sports and ESPN Radio.
